{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I didn't always love unintended consequences,"},{"time":3000,"text":"but I've really learned to appreciate them."},{"time":5000,"text":"I've learned that they're really the essence"},{"time":7000,"text":"of what makes for progress,"},{"time":9000,"text":"even when they seem to be terrible."},{"time":12000,"text":"And I'd like to review"},{"time":14000,"text":"just how unintended consequences"},{"time":17000,"text":"play the part that they do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20000,"text":"Let's go to 40,000 years before the present,"},{"time":25000,"text":"to the time of the cultural explosion,"},{"time":29000,"text":"when music, art, technology,"},{"time":34000,"text":"so many of the things that we're enjoying today,"},{"time":36000,"text":"so many of the things that are being demonstrated at TED"},{"time":39000,"text":"were born."},{"time":41000,"text":"And the anthropologist Randall White"},{"time":44000,"text":"has made a very interesting observation:"},{"time":47000,"text":"that if our ancestors"},{"time":49000,"text":"40,000 years ago"},{"time":51000,"text":"had been able to see"},{"time":54000,"text":"what they had done,"},{"time":56000,"text":"they wouldn't have really understood it."},{"time":58000,"text":"They were responding"},{"time":60000,"text":"to immediate concerns."},{"time":63000,"text":"They were making it possible for us"},{"time":65000,"text":"to do what they do,"},{"time":67000,"text":"and yet, they didn't really understand"},{"time":69000,"text":"how they did it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"Now let's advance to 10,000 years before the present."},{"time":76000,"text":"And this is when it really gets interesting."},{"time":78000,"text":"What about the domestication of grains?"},{"time":81000,"text":"What about the origins of agriculture?"},{"time":84000,"text":"What would our ancestors 10,000 years ago"},{"time":87000,"text":"have said"},{"time":89000,"text":"if they really had technology assessment?"},{"time":91000,"text":"And I could just imagine the committees"},{"time":93000,"text":"reporting back to them"},{"time":95000,"text":"on where agriculture was going to take humanity,"},{"time":98000,"text":"at least in the next few hundred years."},{"time":101000,"text":"It was really bad news."},{"time":103000,"text":"First of all, worse nutrition,"},{"time":105000,"text":"maybe shorter life spans."},{"time":107000,"text":"It was simply awful for women."},{"time":109000,"text":"The skeletal remains from that period"},{"time":111000,"text":"have shown that they were grinding grain morning, noon and night."},{"time":116000,"text":"And politically, it was awful."},{"time":119000,"text":"It was the beginning of a much higher degree"},{"time":122000,"text":"of inequality among people."},{"time":125000,"text":"If there had been rational technology assessment then,"},{"time":128000,"text":"I think they very well might have said,"},{"time":130000,"text":"\"Let's call the whole thing off.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"Even now, our choices are having unintended effects."},{"time":137000,"text":"Historically, for example,"},{"time":139000,"text":"chopsticks -- according to one Japanese anthropologist"},{"time":142000,"text":"who wrote a dissertation about it"},{"time":144000,"text":"at the University of Michigan --"},{"time":146000,"text":"resulted in long-term changes"},{"time":149000,"text":"in the dentition, in the teeth,"},{"time":151000,"text":"of the Japanese public."},{"time":153000,"text":"And we are also changing our teeth right now."},{"time":156000,"text":"There is evidence"},{"time":158000,"text":"that the human mouth and teeth"},{"time":160000,"text":"are growing smaller all the time."},{"time":162000,"text":"That's not necessarily a bad unintended consequence."},{"time":165000,"text":"But I think from the point of view of a Neanderthal,"},{"time":167000,"text":"there would have been a lot of disapproval"},{"time":169000,"text":"of the wimpish choppers that we now have."},{"time":172000,"text":"So these things are kind of relative"},{"time":175000,"text":"to where you or your ancestors happen to stand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"In the ancient world"},{"time":181000,"text":"there was a lot of respect for unintended consequences,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and there was a very healthy sense of caution,"},{"time":187000,"text":"reflected in the Tree of Knowledge,"},{"time":189000,"text":"in Pandora's Box,"},{"time":191000,"text":"and especially in the myth of Prometheus"},{"time":193000,"text":"that's been so important"},{"time":195000,"text":"in recent metaphors about technology."},{"time":197000,"text":"And that's all very true."},{"time":200000,"text":"The physicians of the ancient world --"},{"time":202000,"text":"especially the Egyptians,"},{"time":204000,"text":"who started medicine as we know it --"},{"time":206000,"text":"were very conscious"},{"time":208000,"text":"of what they could and couldn't treat."},{"time":210000,"text":"And the translations of the surviving texts say,"},{"time":215000,"text":"\"This I will not treat. This I cannot treat.\""},{"time":217000,"text":"They were very conscious."},{"time":219000,"text":"So were the followers of Hippocrates."},{"time":221000,"text":"The Hippocratic manuscripts also --"},{"time":223000,"text":"repeatedly, according to recent studies --"},{"time":226000,"text":"show how important it is not to do harm."},{"time":229000,"text":"More recently,"},{"time":231000,"text":"Harvey Cushing,"},{"time":233000,"text":"who really developed neurosurgery as we know it,"},{"time":235000,"text":"who changed it from a field of medicine"},{"time":238000,"text":"that had a majority of deaths resulting from surgery"},{"time":242000,"text":"to one in which there was a hopeful outlook,"},{"time":245000,"text":"he was very conscious"},{"time":247000,"text":"that he was not always going to do the right thing."},{"time":250000,"text":"But he did his best,"},{"time":252000,"text":"and he kept meticulous records"},{"time":254000,"text":"that let him transform that branch of medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"Now if we look forward a bit"},{"time":260000,"text":"to the 19th century,"},{"time":262000,"text":"we find a new style of technology."},{"time":264000,"text":"What we find is,"},{"time":266000,"text":"no longer simple tools,"},{"time":269000,"text":"but systems."},{"time":271000,"text":"We find more and more"},{"time":273000,"text":"complex arrangements of machines"},{"time":275000,"text":"that make it harder and harder"},{"time":277000,"text":"to diagnose what's going on."},{"time":279000,"text":"And the first people who saw that"},{"time":281000,"text":"were the telegraphers of the mid-19th century,"},{"time":284000,"text":"who were the original hackers."},{"time":286000,"text":"Thomas Edison would have been very, very comfortable"},{"time":289000,"text":"in the atmosphere of a software firm today."},{"time":292000,"text":"And these hackers had a word"},{"time":295000,"text":"for those mysterious bugs in telegraph systems"},{"time":298000,"text":"that they called bugs."},{"time":300000,"text":"That was the origin of the word \"bug.\""},{"time":304000,"text":"This consciousness, though,"},{"time":306000,"text":"was a little slow to seep through the general population,"},{"time":309000,"text":"even people who were very, very well informed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312000,"text":"Samuel Clemens, Mark Twain,"},{"time":314000,"text":"was a big investor"},{"time":316000,"text":"in the most complex machine of all times --"},{"time":319000,"text":"at least until 1918 --"},{"time":321000,"text":"registered with the U.S. Patent Office."},{"time":323000,"text":"That was the Paige typesetter."},{"time":325000,"text":"The Paige typesetter"},{"time":327000,"text":"had 18,000 parts."},{"time":329000,"text":"The patent had 64 pages of text"},{"time":332000,"text":"and 271 figures."},{"time":336000,"text":"It was such a beautiful machine"},{"time":338000,"text":"because it did everything that a human being did"},{"time":341000,"text":"in setting type --"},{"time":343000,"text":"including returning the type to its place,"},{"time":345000,"text":"which was a very difficult thing."},{"time":347000,"text":"And Mark Twain, who knew all about typesetting,"},{"time":349000,"text":"really was smitten by this machine."},{"time":352000,"text":"Unfortunately, he was smitten in more ways than one,"},{"time":355000,"text":"because it made him bankrupt,"},{"time":357000,"text":"and he had to tour the world speaking"},{"time":359000,"text":"to recoup his money."},{"time":362000,"text":"And this was an important thing"},{"time":364000,"text":"about 19th century technology,"},{"time":366000,"text":"that all these relationships among parts"},{"time":368000,"text":"could make the most brilliant idea fall apart,"},{"time":372000,"text":"even when judged by the most expert people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374000,"text":"Now there is something else, though, in the early 20th century"},{"time":377000,"text":"that made things even more complicated."},{"time":380000,"text":"And that was that safety technology itself"},{"time":383000,"text":"could be a source of danger."},{"time":385000,"text":"The lesson of the Titanic, for a lot of the contemporaries,"},{"time":388000,"text":"was that you must have enough lifeboats"},{"time":390000,"text":"for everyone on the ship."},{"time":392000,"text":"And this was the result"},{"time":395000,"text":"of the tragic loss of lives"},{"time":397000,"text":"of people who could not get into them."},{"time":399000,"text":"However, there was another case, the Eastland,"},{"time":402000,"text":"a ship that capsized in Chicago Harbor in 1915,"},{"time":406000,"text":"and it killed 841 people --"},{"time":409000,"text":"that was 14 more"},{"time":411000,"text":"than the passenger toll of the Titanic."},{"time":414000,"text":"The reason for it, in part, was"},{"time":416000,"text":"the extra life boats that were added"},{"time":419000,"text":"that made this already unstable ship"},{"time":422000,"text":"even more unstable."},{"time":424000,"text":"And that again proves"},{"time":426000,"text":"that when you're talking about unintended consequences,"},{"time":429000,"text":"it's not that easy to know"},{"time":431000,"text":"the right lessons to draw."},{"time":433000,"text":"It's really a question of the system, how the ship was loaded,"},{"time":436000,"text":"the ballast and many other things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"So the 20th century, then,"},{"time":443000,"text":"saw how much more complex reality was,"},{"time":445000,"text":"but it also saw a positive side."},{"time":448000,"text":"It saw that invention"},{"time":451000,"text":"could actually benefit from emergencies."},{"time":453000,"text":"It could benefit"},{"time":455000,"text":"from tragedies."},{"time":458000,"text":"And my favorite example of that --"},{"time":460000,"text":"which is not really widely known"},{"time":462000,"text":"as a technological miracle,"},{"time":464000,"text":"but it may be one of the greatest of all times,"},{"time":467000,"text":"was the scaling up of penicillin in the Second World War."},{"time":471000,"text":"Penicillin was discovered in 1928,"},{"time":474000,"text":"but even by 1940,"},{"time":476000,"text":"no commercially and medically useful quantities of it"},{"time":479000,"text":"were being produced."},{"time":481000,"text":"A number of pharmaceutical companies were working on it."},{"time":484000,"text":"They were working on it independently,"},{"time":486000,"text":"and they weren't getting anywhere."},{"time":488000,"text":"And the Government Research Bureau"},{"time":490000,"text":"brought representatives together"},{"time":492000,"text":"and told them that this is something"},{"time":494000,"text":"that has to be done."},{"time":496000,"text":"And not only did they do it,"},{"time":498000,"text":"but within two years,"},{"time":500000,"text":"they scaled up penicillin"},{"time":502000,"text":"from preparation in one-liter flasks"},{"time":505000,"text":"to 10,000-gallon vats."},{"time":509000,"text":"That was how quickly penicillin was produced"},{"time":513000,"text":"and became one of the greatest medical advances of all time."},{"time":517000,"text":"In the Second World War, too,"},{"time":519000,"text":"the existence"},{"time":521000,"text":"of solar radiation"},{"time":523000,"text":"was demonstrated by studies of interference"},{"time":526000,"text":"that was detected by the radar stations of Great Britain."},{"time":530000,"text":"So there were benefits in calamities --"},{"time":533000,"text":"benefits to pure science,"},{"time":535000,"text":"as well as to applied science"},{"time":537000,"text":"and medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"Now when we come to the period after the Second World War,"},{"time":543000,"text":"unintended consequences get even more interesting."},{"time":547000,"text":"And my favorite example of that"},{"time":549000,"text":"occurred beginning in 1976,"},{"time":552000,"text":"when it was discovered"},{"time":554000,"text":"that the bacteria causing Legionnaires disease"},{"time":557000,"text":"had always been present in natural waters,"},{"time":560000,"text":"but it was the precise temperature of the water"},{"time":564000,"text":"in heating, ventilating and air conditioning systems"},{"time":567000,"text":"that raised the right temperature"},{"time":571000,"text":"for the maximum reproduction"},{"time":574000,"text":"of Legionella bacillus."},{"time":576000,"text":"Well, technology to the rescue."},{"time":578000,"text":"So chemists got to work,"},{"time":580000,"text":"and they developed a bactericide"},{"time":582000,"text":"that became widely used in those systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"But something else happened in the early 1980s,"},{"time":589000,"text":"and that was that there was a mysterious epidemic"},{"time":591000,"text":"of failures of tape drives"},{"time":594000,"text":"all over the United States."},{"time":596000,"text":"And IBM, which made them,"},{"time":599000,"text":"just didn't know what to do."},{"time":602000,"text":"They commissioned a group of their best scientists"},{"time":605000,"text":"to investigate,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and what they found was"},{"time":609000,"text":"that all these tape drives"},{"time":611000,"text":"were located near ventilation ducts."},{"time":614000,"text":"What happened was the bactericide was formulated"},{"time":617000,"text":"with minute traces of tin."},{"time":619000,"text":"And these tin particles were deposited on the tape heads"},{"time":622000,"text":"and were crashing the tape heads."},{"time":625000,"text":"So they reformulated the bactericide."},{"time":628000,"text":"But what's interesting to me"},{"time":630000,"text":"is that this was the first case"},{"time":632000,"text":"of a mechanical device"},{"time":634000,"text":"suffering, at least indirectly, from a human disease."},{"time":637000,"text":"So it shows that we're really all in this together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"In fact, it also shows something interesting,"},{"time":645000,"text":"that although our capabilities and technology"},{"time":648000,"text":"have been expanding geometrically,"},{"time":650000,"text":"unfortunately, our ability to model their long-term behavior,"},{"time":653000,"text":"which has also been increasing,"},{"time":655000,"text":"has been increasing only arithmetically."},{"time":658000,"text":"So one of the characteristic problems of our time"},{"time":661000,"text":"is how to close this gap"},{"time":663000,"text":"between capabilities and foresight."},{"time":666000,"text":"One other very positive consequence"},{"time":669000,"text":"of 20th century technology, though,"},{"time":672000,"text":"was the way in which other kinds of calamities"},{"time":676000,"text":"could lead to positive advances."},{"time":679000,"text":"There are two historians of business"},{"time":682000,"text":"at the University of Maryland,"},{"time":684000,"text":"Brent Goldfarb and David Kirsch,"},{"time":686000,"text":"who have done some extremely interesting work,"},{"time":688000,"text":"much of it still unpublished,"},{"time":691000,"text":"on the history of major innovations."},{"time":693000,"text":"They have combined the list of major innovations,"},{"time":696000,"text":"and they've discovered that the greatest number, the greatest decade,"},{"time":699000,"text":"for fundamental innovations,"},{"time":701000,"text":"as reflected in all of the lists that others have made --"},{"time":705000,"text":"a number of lists that they have merged --"},{"time":707000,"text":"was the Great Depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710000,"text":"And nobody knows just why this was so,"},{"time":713000,"text":"but one story can reflect something of it."},{"time":716000,"text":"It was the origin of the Xerox copier,"},{"time":719000,"text":"which celebrated its 50th anniversary"},{"time":722000,"text":"last year."},{"time":724000,"text":"And Chester Carlson, the inventor,"},{"time":729000,"text":"was a patent attorney."},{"time":732000,"text":"He really was not intending"},{"time":735000,"text":"to work in patent research,"},{"time":737000,"text":"but he couldn't really find an alternative technical job."},{"time":741000,"text":"So this was the best job he could get."},{"time":743000,"text":"He was upset by the low quality and high cost"},{"time":747000,"text":"of existing patent reproductions,"},{"time":750000,"text":"and so he started to develop"},{"time":753000,"text":"a system of dry photocopying,"},{"time":756000,"text":"which he patented in the late 1930s --"},{"time":759000,"text":"and which became the first dry photocopier"},{"time":763000,"text":"that was commercially practical"},{"time":765000,"text":"in 1960."},{"time":767000,"text":"So we see that sometimes,"},{"time":769000,"text":"as a result of these dislocations,"},{"time":771000,"text":"as a result of people"},{"time":773000,"text":"leaving their original intended career"},{"time":776000,"text":"and going into something else"},{"time":778000,"text":"where their creativity could make a difference,"},{"time":780000,"text":"that depressions"},{"time":782000,"text":"and all kinds of other unfortunate events"},{"time":785000,"text":"can have a paradoxically stimulating effect"},{"time":788000,"text":"on creativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"What does this mean?"},{"time":792000,"text":"It means, I think,"},{"time":794000,"text":"that we're living in a time of unexpected possibilities."},{"time":796000,"text":"Think of the financial world, for example."},{"time":799000,"text":"The mentor of Warren Buffett, Benjamin Graham,"},{"time":802000,"text":"developed his system of value investing"},{"time":807000,"text":"as a result of his own losses"},{"time":809000,"text":"in the 1929 crash."},{"time":811000,"text":"And he published that book"},{"time":813000,"text":"in the early 1930s,"},{"time":816000,"text":"and the book still exists in further editions"},{"time":818000,"text":"and is still a fundamental textbook."},{"time":820000,"text":"So many important creative things can happen"},{"time":824000,"text":"when people learn from disasters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827000,"text":"Now think of the large and small plagues that we have now --"},{"time":831000,"text":"bed bugs, killer bees, spam --"},{"time":836000,"text":"and it's very possible that the solutions to those"},{"time":839000,"text":"will really extend well beyond the immediate question."},{"time":842000,"text":"If we think, for example, of Louis Pasteur,"},{"time":845000,"text":"who in the 1860s"},{"time":847000,"text":"was asked to study"},{"time":849000,"text":"the diseases of silk worms for the silk industry,"},{"time":853000,"text":"and his discoveries were really the beginning"},{"time":856000,"text":"of the germ theory of disease."},{"time":858000,"text":"So very often, some kind of disaster --"},{"time":861000,"text":"sometimes the consequence, for example,"},{"time":864000,"text":"of over-cultivation of silk worms,"},{"time":867000,"text":"which was a problem in Europe at the time --"},{"time":869000,"text":"can be the key to something much bigger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871000,"text":"So this means"},{"time":873000,"text":"that we need to take a different view"},{"time":875000,"text":"of unintended consequences."},{"time":877000,"text":"We need to take a really positive view."},{"time":880000,"text":"We need to see what they can do for us."},{"time":883000,"text":"We need to learn"},{"time":885000,"text":"from those figures that I mentioned."},{"time":887000,"text":"We need to learn, for example, from Dr. Cushing,"},{"time":890000,"text":"who killed patients"},{"time":892000,"text":"in the course of his early operations."},{"time":894000,"text":"He had to have some errors. He had to have some mistakes."},{"time":897000,"text":"And he learned meticulously from his mistakes."},{"time":900000,"text":"And as a result,"},{"time":902000,"text":"when we say, \"This isn't brain surgery,\""},{"time":905000,"text":"that pays tribute to how difficult it was"},{"time":908000,"text":"for anyone to learn from their mistakes"},{"time":910000,"text":"in a field of medicine"},{"time":912000,"text":"that was considered so discouraging in its prospects."},{"time":915000,"text":"And we can also remember"},{"time":918000,"text":"how the pharmaceutical companies"},{"time":920000,"text":"were willing to pool their knowledge,"},{"time":922000,"text":"to share their knowledge,"},{"time":924000,"text":"in the face of an emergency,"},{"time":926000,"text":"which they hadn't really been for years and years."},{"time":929000,"text":"They might have been able to do it earlier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"The message, then, for me,"},{"time":935000,"text":"about unintended consequences"},{"time":937000,"text":"is chaos happens;"},{"time":940000,"text":"let's make better use of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}